about nikos moshovos's poetry 







 nikolaos ioannis moshovos 

poet



nikolaos moshovos was born in 1964 at thessaloniki, greece. he spent
most of his childhood in athens and in serres. in 1974 he returns to
thessaloniki where he starts writting poems and prose.


in 1992, his early poems are published. his collection of poems titled
 "agnantevontas ta oneira, mia poiitiki diadromi 1974-1991" 
draws the attention of several literature related publications and of newspapers
(noymas, anti, eleythero pneyma, giati, makedonia, eleysis etc.).
his second collection of poems, 
 "to petagma toy ianou " 
 was published in november 1995.

many artists have commented on his work. among them are: m. kougioumtzis, akis
gerontakis, michalis peristeraki, michalis katsaros, lampros malamas, and
xrisoula varveri-varra.

he is a member of 15 international and national literature organizations
from greece, france, india, israel, italy, and u.s.a. 

he has has received several awards:  deel  - greece,
 premio san benedetto patrono d'europa, academia fiorino - italy,
 2nd literature award of the lutece international academy  - france and others. his poem
 myrto
won the second place award in the international poetry contest of the valentiana
academy, italy.
finaly, he is the coordinator of the world poetry congress that is going to take
place in 2005 at thessaloniki, greece.

